Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and quarter @zucchini{1}(trimmed and quartered lengthwise); cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick pieces. Trim and thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%oz}(trimmed and sliced). Halve @grape tomatoes{4%oz}(halved). Mince @chives{1/4%oz}(minced). Quarter @lemon{1}(quartered).

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and softened, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Transfer to a #medium bowl{}. Wipe out pan.

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water. Pat shrimp dry with #paper towels{}; season all over with salt and pepper. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add shrimp; cook, stirring occasionally, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Shrimp are fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

Heat a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms and cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown and slightly crispy, ~{5-7%minutes}. Turn off heat; season with salt and pepper. Transfer to #bowl{} with zucchini. Wash out pan.

Use pan used for shrimp here.

Once water is boiling, add @penne pasta{6%oz} to pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water, then drain.

While penne cooks, heat ½ TBSP @butter{1.5%tbsp} and a drizzle of olive oil in pan used for mushrooms over medium-high heat. Add tomatoes and season with @Italian seasoning{1%tbsp}, salt, and pepper. (Use the rest of the Italian seasoning as you like.) Cook, stirring, until tomatoes are softened, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Stir in half the chives and juice from half the lemon. Reduce heat to low, then stir in @mushroom stock concentrate{1} and ¼ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1⁄3 cup for 4).

Whisk in @crème fraîche{3%tbsp}; season with salt and pepper.

Add zucchini, mushrooms, and drained penne to pan with sauce; stir to combine. Stir in 1 TBSP butter until melted. TIP: If necessary, add more pasta cooking water a splash at a time until penne is coated in a creamy sauce.

Divide pasta between #bowls{}. Sprinkle with @Parmesan cheese{1/4%tbsp} and remaining chives. Serve with remaining lemon wedges on the side.

Serve shrimp atop pasta.